<topic id='attribute_clinical_terminology_code.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Attribute: CLINICAL TERMINOLOGY CODE - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
A unique clinical terminology identifier for a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_coded_clinical_entry">CODED CLINICAL ENTRY</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
This could be 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_read_coded_clinical_terms">Read Coded Clinical Terms</xref>, 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_snomed_ct">SNOMED CT</xref>
 concepts or defined in the 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_national_interim_clinical_imaging_procedure_code_set">National Interim Clinical Imaging Procedure Code Set</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
See 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_clinical_coding_introduction">Clinical Coding</xref>
 for further information about the types of 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_coded_clinical_entry">CODED CLINICAL ENTRIES</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
Note: 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_snomed_ct">SNOMED CT</xref>
 is the Information Standard for clinical terminology for use within the NHS; it is planned that in time this will be the only terminology used by the NHS.        </p>
  </div>
